29
00:01:36.760 --> 00:01:40.740
So I'm going to tell you a very exciting journey, which is an unusual

30
00:01:40.860 --> 00:01:44.360
journey because it's an academic journey, going from the discovery of a gene to a

31
00:01:44.440 --> 00:01:47.560
drug that is now FDA approved for three different indications.

32
00:01:48.920 --> 00:01:50.660
Please consider my disclosures.

33
00:01:52.360 --> 00:01:55.960
So as you probably all know, kidney cancer is expected to

34
00:01:56.560 --> 00:01:59.380
be diagnosed in about half a million people worldwide.

35
00:01:59.900 --> 00:02:03.720
Most common type is clear cell renal cell carcinoma, predominantly affects men.

36
00:02:04.260 --> 00:02:06.100
In about 30% of the patients,

37
00:02:06.980 --> 00:02:08.900
it results in metastasis.

38
00:02:09.741 --> 00:02:13.500
And kidney cancer is one of these tumor types that can metastasize pretty

39
00:02:13.560 --> 00:02:17.340
much to every organ. Some of them associated with poor prognosis, some of

40
00:02:17.360 --> 00:02:20.360
them, when it metastasizes to the pancreas, with better prognosis.

41
00:02:22.260 --> 00:02:24.380
This is something that you may be very familiar with.

42
00:02:24.660 --> 00:02:28.240
So it's a cartoon from the "New England Journal of Medicine." Very simple cartoon,

43
00:02:28.320 --> 00:02:32.269
but makes the point about HIF in clear cell renal

44
00:02:32.440 --> 00:02:35.020
cell carcinoma. It plays a critical role downstream of VHL.

45
00:02:35.540 --> 00:02:38.710
And as you know, this paper was recognized with the Nobel Prize in 2019.

46
00:02:39.360 --> 00:02:43.340
It also outlines the different targeted therapies that we have available for

47
00:02:43.380 --> 00:02:43.840
the field.

48
00:02:44.880 --> 00:02:48.600
A HIF2 inhibitor would not only block angiogenesis, but it would also target cell

49
00:02:48.640 --> 00:02:49.520
proliferation,

50
00:02:51.300 --> 00:02:53.420
block pluripotency, and induce apoptosis.

51
00:02:54.780 --> 00:02:58.340
And today, we're talking about bel sutifan, which is a first-in-class

52
00:02:58.740 --> 00:03:00.440
inhibitor targeting HIF-2 alpha.

53
00:03:01.880 --> 00:03:05.840
So HIF-2 alpha was discovered by four different groups including Steve

54
00:03:05.880 --> 00:03:09.370
McKnight, depicted here, who was at the time the chair of

55
00:03:09.380 --> 00:03:13.370
biochemistry at UT Southwestern, and named HIF-2 alpha EH-PAS one, and

56
00:03:13.420 --> 00:03:15.600
this was in 1996.

57
00:03:17.120 --> 00:03:21.100
Subsequent studies at UT Southwestern by Greg Broek and Kevin Gardner

58
00:03:21.800 --> 00:03:25.220
of the PAS-B domain. So the PAS-B domain, as you can see here,

59
00:03:25.800 --> 00:03:29.269
is one of these two domains, the PAS-A and PAS-B, that are important for

60
00:03:29.320 --> 00:03:32.140
dimerization. The HIF-2 transcription factor is a basic

61
00:03:32.240 --> 00:03:35.960
helix-loop-helix heterodimer, here binds the

62
00:03:36.000 --> 00:03:39.280
hypoxia response element. And these two complex

63
00:03:39.360 --> 00:03:41.840
predominantly interact through the PAS-B domain.

64
00:03:42.720 --> 00:03:45.060
So Kevin characterized the structure, and they

65
00:03:46.660 --> 00:03:50.220
were surprised by the identification of a small cavity, depicted here,

66
00:03:50.680 --> 00:03:52.640
within the PAS-B domain of HIF-2 alpha.

67
00:03:53.600 --> 00:03:57.520
And it's unusual for proteins to have an internal cavity, as you can see

68
00:03:57.560 --> 00:03:59.560
depicted here, with water molecules.

69
00:04:00.240 --> 00:04:04.220
So this led them to hypothesize that this could be exploited for drug

70
00:04:04.280 --> 00:04:08.200
development, and they screened the library of compounds that we

71
00:04:08.240 --> 00:04:12.100
have at UT Southwestern, 200,000 compounds, looking for compounds that

72
00:04:12.120 --> 00:04:15.980
were able to engage the cavity and dissociate the purified PAS-B

73
00:04:16.019 --> 00:04:17.820
domain of HIF-2 alpha and HIF-1 beta.

74
00:04:18.661 --> 00:04:22.340
So that led to identification of several lead compounds that were able to

75
00:04:22.360 --> 00:04:25.860
induce an allosteric change in the PAS-B domain to trigger the

76
00:04:25.900 --> 00:04:27.960
dissociation of these purified PAS-B domains.

77
00:04:28.480 --> 00:04:32.440
Which they subsequently show, were able to dissociate the full complex.

78
00:04:34.100 --> 00:04:37.600
So this led Steve McKnight to found a company, Peloton

79
00:04:37.640 --> 00:04:41.600
Therapeutics, in the UT Southwestern Biocenter, so across the street from UT

80
00:04:41.640 --> 00:04:42.260
Southwestern.

81
00:04:43.180 --> 00:04:44.420
So Peloton Therapeutics

82
00:04:45.360 --> 00:04:48.960
leveraged these insights to develop several inhibitors,

83
00:04:49.540 --> 00:04:51.640
and I'm going to talk to you today about three of them.

84
00:04:51.860 --> 00:04:55.600
So you have this one over here, PT-2385. This is the first in human.

85
00:04:56.100 --> 00:04:58.580
PT-2399, this is the tool compound.

86
00:04:59.050 --> 00:05:02.820
And then PT-2977, this was renamed bel sutifan by

87
00:05:02.880 --> 00:05:06.820
Merck. And as you can see, the overall structure of these

88
00:05:06.860 --> 00:05:08.180
compounds is similar.

89
00:05:09.340 --> 00:05:13.020
So to ask whether these compounds would have activity against kidney

90
00:05:13.040 --> 00:05:16.040
cancer, we leverage our tumor graft platform.

91
00:05:16.480 --> 00:05:20.460
So these are patient tumors implanted in mice, and Bill Kelen

92
00:05:20.480 --> 00:05:22.160
was doing these experiments in cell lines.

93
00:05:22.940 --> 00:05:25.430
So over the course of the years, we have implanted tumors.

94
00:05:25.560 --> 00:05:26.420
Now we are, in fact,

95
00:05:27.340 --> 00:05:29.640
over 2,000 samples

96
00:05:30.800 --> 00:05:34.300
from about the same number of patients orthotopically in mice.

97
00:05:34.940 --> 00:05:38.360
And these tumors are implanted without any additives or

98
00:05:38.400 --> 00:05:41.700
disaggregation, and we've used them for a variety of applications.

99
00:05:42.320 --> 00:05:46.280
So we use this platform. I'm just showing here an example of a tumor

100
00:05:46.340 --> 00:05:49.140
that was treated with vehicle sunitinib to match human

101
00:05:49.150 --> 00:05:53.080
exposures here in green, and then this HIF-2

102
00:05:53.100 --> 00:05:56.680
inhibitor, PT-2399. And as you can see, it caused

103
00:05:56.920 --> 00:06:00.904
significant regression.So these experiments were done in a large

104
00:06:00.944 --> 00:06:04.584
cohort of mice, so 267 mice from

105
00:06:04.844 --> 00:06:08.644
22 independently derived tumor graph lines, most of

106
00:06:08.684 --> 00:06:11.404
them from clear cell renal cell carcinoma tumors.

107
00:06:12.144 --> 00:06:15.664
And we found that overall, compared to sunitinib, this HIF-2

108
00:06:15.684 --> 00:06:19.004
inhibitor resulted in greater tumor regression,

109
00:06:19.704 --> 00:06:21.764
and in addition, was better tolerated.

110
00:06:21.864 --> 00:06:25.544
You can see here that the mice treated with sunitinib lost weight, whereas the mice

111
00:06:25.604 --> 00:06:29.554
treated with PT-2399 did not. And in the clinic we often see that sunitinib is

112
00:06:29.584 --> 00:06:33.424
associated with diarrhea and loss of appetite and other problems.

113
00:06:34.904 --> 00:06:38.744
So this data set the foundation for a multi-institutional phase

114
00:06:38.824 --> 00:06:42.344
one clinical trial that Brian participated in.

115
00:06:43.164 --> 00:06:45.044
And I'm just going to show you one piece of data.

116
00:06:45.184 --> 00:06:48.414
So this, you can see here the famous plot, about 50 patients or so,

117
00:06:49.144 --> 00:06:50.933
of course, heavily pre-treated patients.

118
00:06:51.124 --> 00:06:54.994
And you can see that approximately 20% of the patients or so were on

119
00:06:55.084 --> 00:06:56.884
treatment for over a year.

120
00:06:57.964 --> 00:07:00.744
There was one complete response and six partial responses.

121
00:07:01.284 --> 00:07:04.824
So this suggested that this drug was going to be active, and it was very well

122
00:07:04.904 --> 00:07:08.684
tolerated. In fact, it went up to 1,800 milligrams twice

123
00:07:08.724 --> 00:07:12.324
daily. If you have that much Tylenol, you probably kill yourself.

124
00:07:14.504 --> 00:07:18.214
So in a companion study, we performed biopsies from

125
00:07:18.224 --> 00:07:21.824
patients pre-treatment and on treatment, and this is a proximity ligation assay.

126
00:07:21.884 --> 00:07:25.704
And as you can see that on the on-treatment biopsies, there is a reduction of these

127
00:07:25.744 --> 00:07:27.624
red dots, which are HIF-2 complexes.

128
00:07:28.044 --> 00:07:32.024
This is quantitated here, and by gene expression analysis, we could see that there

129
00:07:32.044 --> 00:07:35.004
is a decrease in the HIF-2 gene expression program.

130
00:07:36.264 --> 00:07:40.164
Peloton made the observation that there was a group of patients here in red that

131
00:07:40.204 --> 00:07:43.804
had lower levels of the PT-2385, and that this

132
00:07:43.844 --> 00:07:46.724
correlated with worse progression-free survival.

133
00:07:46.804 --> 00:07:50.184
So they thought that this might be the result of rapid

134
00:07:50.244 --> 00:07:53.254
metabolism, and that led to development of

135
00:07:53.264 --> 00:07:54.634
PT-2977,

136
00:07:55.464 --> 00:07:59.144
which actually has better pharmacokinetic properties, has a slightly higher

137
00:07:59.204 --> 00:08:02.744
affinity. But as you can see here, this is our studies in non-human

138
00:08:02.824 --> 00:08:03.244
primates.

139
00:08:04.104 --> 00:08:06.743
It has significantly better AUC.

140
00:08:08.484 --> 00:08:11.964
So Peloton was acquired by Merck, who

141
00:08:12.064 --> 00:08:15.344
renamed PT-2977 bel sutiban.

142
00:08:16.084 --> 00:08:19.384
And I'm not going to go through this data because Eric is going to go into a lot of

143
00:08:19.444 --> 00:08:22.984
detail, but this has revolutionized the treatment of

144
00:08:23.044 --> 00:08:23.964
VHL patients.

145
00:08:24.784 --> 00:08:28.444
The drug was approved by the FDA in 2021.

146
00:08:28.934 --> 00:08:32.584
This is the first patient that I treated, a patient that had, as you can see

147
00:08:32.664 --> 00:08:36.485
here, this cerebellar hemangioblastoma, including a large one that was

148
00:08:36.544 --> 00:08:38.704
symptomatic with headaches, and a second one here.

149
00:08:39.184 --> 00:08:42.784
And after a few months on treatment, she was doing remarkably better.

150
00:08:42.865 --> 00:08:46.844
In fact, she started feeling quite well soon after the

151
00:08:46.904 --> 00:08:47.864
start of the treatment.

152
00:08:49.724 --> 00:08:53.464
And of course, you'll hear from Brian, this drug has also shown

153
00:08:54.264 --> 00:08:55.044
improvements

154
00:08:56.244 --> 00:08:59.464
in comparison to everolimus in sporadic

155
00:08:59.804 --> 00:09:03.204
patients. But what I want to point out is that

156
00:09:04.964 --> 00:09:08.364
30% of the patients have a primary progressive disease,

157
00:09:08.464 --> 00:09:12.184
so it is important for us to try to devise strategies to

158
00:09:12.204 --> 00:09:15.944
identify these patients. So the approach that we took

159
00:09:16.084 --> 00:09:19.824
was ask how are these tumors in the mice different,

160
00:09:20.274 --> 00:09:22.184
those that are sensitive from those that are resistant?

161
00:09:22.224 --> 00:09:26.044
And what we found is that the tumors that were sensitive had significantly higher

162
00:09:26.084 --> 00:09:29.864
levels of HIF-2 alpha than the tumors that were resistant here in red,

163
00:09:29.964 --> 00:09:32.484
quantitated here by Western blot,

164
00:09:33.984 --> 00:09:37.744
and that was also true at the mRNA

165
00:09:37.764 --> 00:09:39.004
level, which I'm not showing here.

166
00:09:39.484 --> 00:09:43.084
So this led us to hypothesize that HIF-2 alpha itself could be a

167
00:09:43.124 --> 00:09:45.184
biomarker, a predictive biomarker of response.

168
00:09:46.084 --> 00:09:48.664
So based on that, and the fact that

169
00:09:49.724 --> 00:09:53.584
these drugs have several fluorine atoms, as you can see here, we

170
00:09:53.604 --> 00:09:57.364
leverage our cyclotron to generate an F18

171
00:09:57.464 --> 00:10:01.164
labeled version of PT-2385, and then we

172
00:10:01.204 --> 00:10:05.164
tested it in mice. So we implanted mice with tumors that either

173
00:10:05.224 --> 00:10:08.904
had low levels of HIF-2 alpha. You can see there is very little nuclear signal.

174
00:10:08.924 --> 00:10:12.904
This is background staining. These high HIF-2 alpha expressing tumors

175
00:10:12.984 --> 00:10:15.443
implanted in the left and the right respectively.

176
00:10:15.464 --> 00:10:18.444
And when we do the pet analysis, you can see that we are able to

177
00:10:18.504 --> 00:10:22.324
identify the HIF-2 alpha expressing tumor, which is consistent

178
00:10:22.384 --> 00:10:25.124
with the high specificity of the drug.

179
00:10:27.204 --> 00:10:30.484
But as you can also see here, the kinetics are actually very quick.

180
00:10:32.244 --> 00:10:36.194
So this led us to submit an IND to the FDA, which

181
00:10:36.264 --> 00:10:40.144
got approved, and we have a clinical trial ongoing with these

182
00:10:40.184 --> 00:10:41.084
tracer in patients.

183
00:10:42.464 --> 00:10:46.284
One of the concerns with targeted therapies is the development of resistance,

184
00:10:46.704 --> 00:10:49.784
and we found that this was indeed the case.

185
00:10:49.874 --> 00:10:53.844
So this is a patient of mine that I think he got treated

186
00:10:53.924 --> 00:10:55.234
after five lines of therapy

187
00:10:56.164 --> 00:10:59.304
and did quite well. But if you look at the skin lesion, even though there was no

188
00:10:59.384 --> 00:11:02.984
resist progression, it started getting filled up, and he

189
00:11:03.024 --> 00:11:06.684
consented to a protocol that we had, and we did biopsy of that

190
00:11:06.724 --> 00:11:10.624
lesion, and we found at this position in the coding sequence of HIF-2 alpha

191
00:11:10.684 --> 00:11:12.044
that there were two different peaks.

192
00:11:12.624 --> 00:11:16.244
We were able to see the mutation also by next

193
00:11:16.284 --> 00:11:20.104
generation sequencing, and if we compare the pre-treatment sample, the mutation

194
00:11:20.164 --> 00:11:24.084
was not there. So this is a mutation that is in

195
00:11:24.224 --> 00:11:26.464
fact, and this is data from

196
00:11:27.944 --> 00:11:31.324
Friedun Gradstein had, is a mutation that is occurring.

197
00:11:31.374 --> 00:11:35.224
It's actually filling up the pocket that is bound by the drug.

198
00:11:36.144 --> 00:11:39.824
And indeed, when we do this proximity ligation assays, we find that in

199
00:11:39.844 --> 00:11:40.844
contrast to

200
00:11:41.944 --> 00:11:43.204
pre-resistant samples,

201
00:11:44.004 --> 00:11:47.724
then HIF-2 complex numbers remain the same,

202
00:11:48.244 --> 00:11:52.144
and we can see that there is reactivation of the HIF-2 alpha

203
00:11:52.184 --> 00:11:54.944
gene expression program in these resistant tumors.

204
00:11:55.584 --> 00:11:59.224
Interestingly enough, the resistance mutations had been previously

205
00:11:59.304 --> 00:12:00.664
identified in tumor graphs.

206
00:12:01.584 --> 00:12:05.564
So we had had, I'm showing you data here for a tumor graph line

207
00:12:05.704 --> 00:12:08.184
XP164 that was sensitive to different mice.

208
00:12:08.684 --> 00:12:11.904
And after treatment for about six months, you can see that these tumors were

209
00:12:11.924 --> 00:12:15.624
growing quite substantially. In immunoprecipitation experiments, we could

210
00:12:15.664 --> 00:12:18.834
show that the HIF-2 complex, which was

211
00:12:18.864 --> 00:12:22.580
dissociatedpre-resistant and

212
00:12:22.700 --> 00:12:26.530
reformed in these two tumors, and we found the same

213
00:12:26.600 --> 00:12:29.640
mutation that we later found in patients.

214
00:12:29.700 --> 00:12:33.340
In addition, we found a second mutation in HIF1 beta, this

215
00:12:33.540 --> 00:12:37.400
phenylalanine to leucine mutation, which is at the surface between

216
00:12:37.420 --> 00:12:41.080
HIF1 beta and HIF2 alpha, and it increases the affinity

217
00:12:41.420 --> 00:12:42.340
of the dimer.

218
00:12:44.400 --> 00:12:48.340
There have been a number of other small molecule HIF2 alpha inhibitors

219
00:12:48.460 --> 00:12:52.260
that target the same pocket. Some of them are no longer in

220
00:12:52.319 --> 00:12:54.780
development, but some of them are.

221
00:12:55.340 --> 00:12:59.160
Casat gefan, for example, BPI, it's

222
00:12:59.400 --> 00:13:01.080
an inhibitor developed in China.

223
00:13:02.380 --> 00:13:06.120
And this NIKAN compound, I don't think is being developed in the US anymore.

224
00:13:07.220 --> 00:13:10.760
The only one that I'm aware of that has activity against the

225
00:13:10.820 --> 00:13:13.000
resistant mutants is the NIKAN compound.

226
00:13:13.640 --> 00:13:17.220
And of course, at this meeting, we have heard about

