01:03:08.504 --> 01:03:12.444
sometimes a bit random. But cabo is a really well-established second-line drug

1094
01:03:12.484 --> 01:03:15.624
and had not been beaten in multiple studies.

1095
01:03:15.684 --> 01:03:19.324
So it was the right comparator. Again, 750 patients.

1096
01:03:19.364 --> 01:03:22.644
You could see with that highlighted bullet points that they had to have

1097
01:03:25.244 --> 01:03:28.744
failed prior immune therapy, and many had prior TKIs, as again, is common.

1098
01:03:29.484 --> 01:03:33.344
Len-belzu at standard doses versus cabo, PFS and OS, so very standard

1099
01:03:33.564 --> 01:03:34.444
Phase III design.

1100
01:03:35.944 --> 01:03:36.264
This is the

1101
01:03:37.204 --> 01:03:41.064
PFS primary endpoint, and again, you see some of the shape here

1102
01:03:41.224 --> 01:03:43.824
is similar to 005. You see some overlap up front.

1103
01:03:44.184 --> 01:03:47.864
Here you do see a difference in the median of about four months, and you

1104
01:03:47.944 --> 01:03:50.684
see the hazard ratio of 0.7, so a significant

1105
01:03:50.704 --> 01:03:54.684
difference in PFS. These lenva and cabo

1106
01:03:54.704 --> 01:03:58.664
are not identical TKIs, but there's no real reason to believe that lenva is

1107
01:03:58.704 --> 01:04:01.544
much better than cabo. I don't know that that's a thing. We could talk about it.

1108
01:04:02.344 --> 01:04:05.484
So it's really, obviously, what is belzutifan adding in this setting?

1109
01:04:06.204 --> 01:04:09.434
I put this blue arrow because you see, again, this is sort of when I first saw

1110
01:04:09.464 --> 01:04:13.024
these data, I said, "Gee, it's not just a difference in the median and hazard

1111
01:04:13.044 --> 01:04:16.944
ratio." You're starting to see this tail of the curve and a doubling at two years.

1112
01:04:17.204 --> 01:04:20.424
Again, a refractory setting, a third of patients still progression-free at two

1113
01:04:20.464 --> 01:04:21.164
