1135
01:05:35.424 --> 01:05:37.564
but they're really good at disease control up front.

1136
01:05:37.604 --> 01:05:39.724
So that's probably one of the biggest advantages here.

1137
01:05:39.764 --> 01:05:43.524
Again, if you have a refractory patient with bulky symptomatic disease, I'd be a

1138
01:05:43.564 --> 01:05:45.304
little nervous about belzu monotherapy.

1139
01:05:45.364 --> 01:05:45.444
I

1140
01:05:46.264 --> 01:05:48.504
would not be nervous about a TKI-containing regimen.

1141
01:05:49.604 --> 01:05:51.204
Again, duration of response, same thing.

1142
01:05:51.224 --> 01:05:54.944
We're seeing two-year duration of response, which is about what we see with the IO

1143
01:05:55.024 --> 01:05:57.764
TKI regimens. It's almost identical.

1144
01:05:57.844 --> 01:06:01.664
So a non-immune therapy containing regimen producing fairly durable

1145
01:06:01.674 --> 01:06:05.004
responses, I think is notable. And again, you see a doubling,

1146
01:06:05.484 --> 01:06:07.204
50% durability at two years.

1147
01:06:08.664 --> 01:06:11.864
And then the other big data set presented was LightSpark-022.

1148
01:06:11.904 --> 01:06:15.764
Merck basically put belzutifan in the water across every kidney

1149
01:06:15.824 --> 01:06:16.284
cancer

1150
01:06:17.804 --> 01:06:19.744
scenario and hits on almost all of them.

1151
01:06:21.164 --> 01:06:24.144
So this was presented. This is in the adjuvant setting where many of you know that

1152
01:06:24.164 --> 01:06:28.004
pembrolizumab monotherapy, which was the control arm of this trial, is the standard

1153
01:06:28.024 --> 01:06:31.404
of care from KEYNOTE-564 at high-risk resected kidney

1154
01:06:31.444 --> 01:06:34.424
cancer. This is now adding belzutifan.

1155
01:06:34.684 --> 01:06:37.224
I famously predicted this trial would be wildly negative.

1156
01:06:37.284 --> 01:06:40.224
I was absolutely wrong about that. You can't get them all right.

1157
01:06:40.284 --> 01:06:44.132
So this is basically the same criteria aspembro

1158
01:06:44.172 --> 01:06:46.372
monotherapy as the KEYNOTE-564 study.

1159
01:06:46.772 --> 01:06:50.061
Huge study, over 1,800 patients, year pembro, year

1160
01:06:50.192 --> 01:06:53.012
pembro/belzu, DFS as primary endpoint.

1161
01:06:54.832 --> 01:06:58.742
And so this is the initial DFS result showing a significant reduction in

1162
01:06:58.772 --> 01:07:00.732
the risk of recurrence in these patients.

1163
01:07:00.832 --> 01:07:04.222
Hazard ratio is 0.72. You could see about a 6% or

